ny-ps5-pro-playstation-5-preorder-buy-price-release-date</id><author><name>安东尼奥·G·迪·贝内代托</name></author></entry><entry><published>2024-09-26T09:04:58-04:00</published><updated> 2024-09-26T09:04:58-04:00</updated><title>谷歌表示，封闭的广告生态系统并不反竞争，只是更安全</title><content type="html">&lt;figure>; &lt;img alt=&quot;充满不同产品广告的页面的照片拼贴。&quot; src=&quot;https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/EYoCD2dVVOPswMEqU4z1H-9akkw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73612180/STK445_ADVERTISING_STK093_GOOGLE_A.0 .jpg&quot; />; &lt;figcaption>;图片：Cath Virginia / The Verge、Getty Images&lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p id=&quot;v6Q71c&quot;>;谷歌本周在法庭上借鉴了一本熟悉的剧本，为自己辩护通过提出安全问题来实施反竞争行为。虽然政府声称其锁定广告技术市场是为了赚更多钱，但谷歌的证人表示，更封闭的生态系统对于用户来说往往更安全——这与谷歌和苹果对其移动应用商店的辩护相呼应。&lt;/p>; &lt; p id=&quot;mthekO&quot;>;谷歌的律师在过去几天里一直在针对司法部进行辩护。该公司辩称，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/24/24253293/google-ad-tech-antitrust-trial-doj-case&quot;>;司法部将其行为视为反竞争行为&lt;/a>; — 例如&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/11/24241386/former-news-corp-executive-google-doj-ad-tech-Trial&quot;>;锁定客户其服务&lt;/a>;并发挥&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/9/24240386/google-doj-ad-tech-antitrust-trial-court-day-one&quot; >;通过其主导地位控制行业规则&lt;/a>;——实际上有正当的商业目的。要点...&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/26/24253523/google-close-ad-ecosystem-awbid-ad-fraud-3ve &quot;>;继续阅读&amp;hellip;&lt;/a>; &lt;/p>; </content><link href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/26/24253523/google-closed-ad-ecosystem-awbid-ad-fraud-3ve" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><id> https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/26/24253523/google-close-ad-ecosystem-awbid-ad-fraud-3ve</id><author><name>劳伦·费纳</name></author></entry></feed>